# ==============================================================================
# PopKit Cloud - Cloudflare Workers Environment Variables (.dev.vars)
# ==============================================================================
#
# FILE: apps/popkit/packages/cloud/.dev.vars.template
# PURPOSE: Template for local development environment variables
# USAGE: Copy to .dev.vars and fill in your Upstash credentials
#
# IMPORTANT: .dev.vars is for LOCAL DEVELOPMENT ONLY (wrangler dev)
# For production, use: wrangler secret put VARIABLE_NAME
#
# LOADING: Cloudflare Workers automatically loads .dev.vars during wrangler dev
# HIERARCHY: .dev.vars (local dev) → wrangler.toml vars → wrangler secrets (production)
#
# ==============================================================================

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Upstash Redis (REQUIRED)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Purpose: Pattern storage, Power Mode coordination, inter-agent messaging
# Get from: https://console.upstash.com/redis
# Plans: Free tier available (10k commands/day)

UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=https://your-redis-instance.upstash.io
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=your_redis_rest_token_here

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Upstash Vector (REQUIRED for semantic search)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Purpose: Semantic agent search, pattern matching, embeddings
# Get from: https://console.upstash.com/vector
# Plans: Free tier available (10k queries/day)
# Related: Issue #101 - Semantic Agent Discovery

UPSTASH_VECTOR_REST_URL=https://your-vector-db.upstash.io
UPSTASH_VECTOR_REST_TOKEN=your_vector_rest_token_here

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Upstash QStash (OPTIONAL - for durable workflows)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Purpose: Scheduled jobs, durable workflows, async task execution
# Get from: https://console.upstash.com/qstash
# Plans: Free tier available (100 messages/day)
# Related: Issue #103 - Durable Workflow System

# QStash API Token (required for workflow features)
QSTASH_TOKEN=your_qstash_token_here

# QStash Signing Keys (optional - for webhook signature verification)
# QSTASH_CURRENT_SIGNING_KEY=your_current_signing_key
# QSTASH_NEXT_SIGNING_KEY=your_next_signing_key

# ==============================================================================
# Setup Instructions
# ==============================================================================
#
# 1. Create Upstash Account (free tier available):
#    https://console.upstash.com/
#
# 2. Create Redis Database:
#    - Go to Redis → Create Database
#    - Select region closest to your users
#    - Copy REST URL and TOKEN
#
# 3. Create Vector Database:
#    - Go to Vector → Create Database
#    - Select embedding model (OpenAI ada-002 recommended)
#    - Copy REST URL and TOKEN
#
# 4. (Optional) Create QStash:
#    - Go to QStash → Get Started
#    - Copy API Token
#
# 5. Copy this template:
#    cp .dev.vars.template .dev.vars
#
# 6. Fill in your credentials in .dev.vars
#
# 7. Start development server:
#    pnpm dev
#    # OR: wrangler dev
#
# ==============================================================================
# Production Deployment
# ==============================================================================
#
# DO NOT commit .dev.vars to git (already in .gitignore)
#
# For production deployment, use wrangler secrets:
#
#   wrangler secret put UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL
#   wrangler secret put UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN
#   wrangler secret put UPSTASH_VECTOR_REST_URL
#   wrangler secret put UPSTASH_VECTOR_REST_TOKEN
#   wrangler secret put QSTASH_TOKEN
#
# Secrets are encrypted and stored securely in Cloudflare Workers
#
# ==============================================================================
# Security Notes
# ==============================================================================
#
# - .dev.vars is gitignored (never commit credentials!)
# - Use separate Upstash databases for dev/staging/production
# - Rotate tokens regularly
# - Enable Upstash IP whitelisting for production
# - Monitor usage at console.upstash.com
#
# ==============================================================================
